---
name: Pull Request
about: Create a pull request to merge a change into the main branch.
title: "<type>: <a brief, descriptive title>"
labels: ''
assignees: ''

---

### Description

Please describe the changes you made and the reason for them.

### Related Issue

This pull request resolves/closes the following issue: #`[issue number]`

### Type of change

* [ ] Bug fix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)
* [ ] New feature (non-breaking change which adds functionality)
* [ ] Breaking change (fix or feature that would cause existing functionality to not work as expected)
* [ ] This change requires a documentation update

### Checklist

Please check all that apply.

* [ ] I have read the [CONTRIBUTING.md](https://github.com/mocky-balboa/mocky-balboa/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md) file.
* [ ] I have added tests that prove my fix is effective or that my feature works.
* [ ] I have added/updated documentation as required.
* [ ] All new and existing tests pass locally.
* [ ] I have rebased my branch on the latest `main`.
* [ ] My code follows the project's style guidelines.

### Examples

**Correct Title Examples:**
* `feat: add network mocking for SSR`
* `fix: resolve issue with invalid headers`
* `chore: update dependencies`
* `docs: add new guide for browser automation`

**Correct "Related Issue" Examples:**
* `Closes #123`
* `Resolves #456`

### Additional Context

Add any other relevant information here.
